00:40:09,560 --> 00:40:11,760
It concerns a man's freedom and sentence.

855
00:40:11,760 --> 00:40:12,550
We thought

856
00:40:12,590 --> 00:40:14,790
we had to meet the judge, no matter what,

857
00:40:14,800 --> 00:40:16,680
to present our defense in person.

858
00:40:20,110 --> 00:40:22,240
Judge Wu has just come back from a case.

859
00:40:22,240 --> 00:40:22,960
Hold on.

860
00:40:24,640 --> 00:40:25,640
There's a chance.

861
00:40:26,730 --> 00:40:28,460
Don't get too excited just yet.

862
00:40:34,610 --> 00:40:35,090
Come in.

863
00:40:35,300 --> 00:40:37,270
Judge Wu, why are you eating now?

864
00:40:38,080 --> 00:40:38,800
They're here?

865
00:40:38,800 --> 00:40:39,600
Let them in.

866
00:40:39,920 --> 00:40:40,560
Come in.

867
00:40:42,360 --> 00:40:43,280
Sorry.

868
00:40:43,310 --> 00:40:43,950
Hello.

869
00:40:43,970 --> 00:40:46,160
The last case took seven hours.

870
00:40:46,300 --> 00:40:47,830
I didn't have time for lunch.

871
00:40:47,830 --> 00:40:48,700
Sorry to bother you.

872
00:40:48,700 --> 00:40:49,450
It's okay.

873
00:40:49,630 --> 00:40:51,720
This way, your worries will be unnecessary.

874
00:40:51,720 --> 00:40:53,290
Please trust the court.

875
00:40:53,420 --> 00:40:54,500
Trust the law.

876
00:40:54,940 --> 00:40:55,920
We will

877
00:40:55,950 --> 00:40:57,420
take your defense seriously.

878
00:40:57,420 --> 00:40:59,070
I'm sorry, Judge Wu.

879
00:40:59,360 --> 00:41:02,420
It's not that we don't trust the court or the law.

880
00:41:02,910 --> 00:41:03,840
But this case

881
00:41:03,860 --> 00:41:05,460
is really important to us.

882
00:41:05,780 --> 00:41:07,540
We're both new lawyers.

883
00:41:07,610 --> 00:41:08,470
The defendant in this case

884
00:41:08,470 --> 00:41:10,360
was sentenced to life in the first instance.

885
00:41:10,360 --> 00:41:12,890
And now our client asks us to plead not guilty.

886
00:41:13,040 --> 00:41:14,360
So, we would like to

887
00:41:14,390 --> 00:41:15,790
present our defense opinions

888
00:41:15,790 --> 00:41:17,820
to you.

889
00:41:18,150 --> 00:41:20,350
Or we'll feel guilty.

890
00:41:21,040 --> 00:41:21,550
I see.

891
00:41:21,620 --> 00:41:22,470
Please sit down.

892
00:41:22,470 --> 00:41:23,470
Sit down and talk.

893
00:41:23,510 --> 00:41:25,050
Xu, you take notes.

894
00:41:25,160 --> 00:41:25,520
Okay.

895
00:41:25,550 --> 00:41:27,250
Here are your defense opinions.

896
00:41:27,250 --> 00:41:28,210
Sit down and talk.

897
00:41:28,210 --> 00:41:29,070
I'm listening.

898
00:41:32,520 --> 00:41:33,210
Judge Wu.

899
00:41:33,680 --> 00:41:34,600
We believe that in the first instance,

900
00:41:34,600 --> 00:41:36,840
the fact that our client, Xu Jianshe, was the main offender

901
00:41:36,840 --> 00:41:37,590
and that the victim

902
00:41:37,590 --> 00:41:39,800
was beaten to death by Xu Jianshe

903
00:41:39,900 --> 00:41:42,180
was not supported by sufficient evidence,

904
00:41:42,180 --> 00:41:44,180
leaving room for reasonable doubt.

905
00:41:44,310 --> 00:41:45,260
At the crime scene,

906
00:41:45,260 --> 00:41:46,300
only Xu Jianshe

907
00:41:46,330 --> 00:41:48,640
and another defendant, Zhang Yulin, were there.

908
00:41:48,640 --> 00:41:49,570
The only direct evidence

909
00:41:49,570 --> 00:41:52,350
that Xu Jianshe killed the victim

910
00:41:52,390 --> 00:41:54,050
is Zhang Yulin's confession.

911
00:41:54,820 --> 00:41:56,030
As a co-suspect,

912
00:41:56,130 --> 00:41:58,720
the credibility of his confession is limited.

913
00:41:58,720 --> 00:42:00,080
Besides his confession,

914
00:42:00,080 --> 00:42:01,390
there is no other direct evidence

915
00:42:01,390 --> 00:42:03,510
to prove that the fact of the first instance is true.

916
00:42:03,510 --> 00:42:05,640
So the chain of evidence is not closed.

917
00:42:08,060 --> 00:42:10,420
All right, I heard your opinions.

918
00:42:10,620 --> 00:42:11,230
Go back.

919
00:42:11,820 --> 00:42:12,680
Trust the law.

920
00:42:12,980 --> 00:42:13,750
Trust us.

921
00:42:14,120 --> 00:42:16,730
We'll do our job according to the law.

922
00:42:17,110 --> 00:42:17,840
Judge Wu.

923
00:42:18,040 --> 00:42:19,440
Strategically,

924
00:42:19,560 --> 00:42:21,070
we should plead for a misdemeanor

925
00:42:21,070 --> 00:42:22,170
for our client.

926
00:42:22,760 --> 00:42:25,740
He insisted that he had gone there to stop the fight,

927
00:42:25,980 --> 00:42:27,580
but on a dark night like that,

928
00:42:27,690 --> 00:42:30,350
it's hard to say he wasn't involved in the fight.

929
00:42:30,550 --> 00:42:33,750
We advised him repeatedly to allow us
to plead for a misdemeanor on his behalf.

930
00:42:33,750 --> 00:42:35,640
But he insisted on pleading not guilty.

931
00:42:35,640 --> 00:42:36,960
We've been discussing

932
00:42:37,630 --> 00:42:39,680
why he is willing to take the risk

933
00:42:39,710 --> 00:42:41,990
of insisting on his innocence.

934
00:42:42,760 --> 00:42:44,690
I think there are only two reasons.

935
00:42:44,790 --> 00:42:45,750
First,

936
00:42:46,970 --> 00:42:48,230
he's really innocent.

937
00:42:48,990 --> 00:42:49,450
Second,

938
00:42:49,920 --> 00:42:51,180
he believes in the law.

939
00:42:52,450 --> 00:42:54,390
Judge Wu, I hope

940
00:42:55,270 --> 00:42:58,160
the law will live up to a man's expectations.
